**ðŸ’¡ Tip for the future:**

When running docker run interactively, you can avoid creating files as root by specifying the user:

```
docker run --rm -it -v "$PWD":/app -w /app -u $(id -u):$(id -g) python:3.12-slim bash
```

This way, all files created in /app will be owned by your Codespace user.